.TH "omap_cm_wait_module_ready" 9 "omap_cm_wait_module_ready" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
omap_cm_wait_module_ready \- wait for a module to leave idle or standby
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" omap_cm_wait_module_ready
.BI "(u8 part "  ","
.BI "s16 prcm_mod "  ","
.BI "u16 idlest_reg "  ","
.BI "u8 idlest_shift "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "part" 12
PRCM partition
.IP "prcm_mod" 12
PRCM module offset
.IP "idlest_reg" 12
CM_IDLESTx register
.IP "idlest_shift" 12
shift of the bit in the CM_IDLEST* register to check
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Wait for the PRCM to indicate that the module identified by
(\fIprcm_mod\fP, \fIidlest_id\fP, \fIidlest_shift\fP) is clocked.  Return 0 upon
success, -EBUSY if the module doesn't enable in time, or -EINVAL if
no per-SoC \fBwait_module_ready\fP function pointer has been registered
or if the idlest register is unknown on the SoC.
